y after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":35,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":44,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705189,"age":79,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. William de Haigh was born about 1180, in England. She had at least 1 daughter with William de Haigh."},"et":{"about 1180–":"umbes 1180–Surnud","1175–Male":"1175–Surnud","1220–1292":"1220–1292","1180–Female":"1180–Surnud","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","about 1180":"umbes 1180","1220":"1220","1175":"1175","1292":"1292","30 December 1220":"30. detsember 1220","1180":"1180","Haigh, Lancashire, England":"Haigh, Lancashire, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1180–":"noin 1180–Kuollut","1175–M